article.description: New Mexico St. 100, W. New Mexico 76
article.headline: New Mexico St. 100, W. New Mexico 76
article.linkText: New Mexico St. 100, W. New Mexico 76
article.story: strsmb LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) -- Justin Hawkins scored 24 points to help New Mexico State overcome a late surge and beat Western New Mexico 100-76 Thursday night. Hawkins, who matched his career high point total, scored 15 points in the first half. He was 8 of 11 from the field and led the Aggies (8-3) with eight assists and four steals. NMSU extended their winning streak to seven games, their longest since the 1998-1999 season when the team had seven- and eight-game streaks. The Mustangs (4-6) trailed by as many as 30 in the first half but pulled within 53-44 when they scored the first eight points of the second half. The drive was capped by Trey Clarkson's 14th point of the night with 17:43 to play. A few minutes later, Western New Mexico pulled within 63-58 when Casey Crevelone hit a 3-pointer from the corner. NMSU followed with a 9-0 run that included Hawkins and Fred Peete putting back missed free throws for baskets. Peete's put back gave the Aggies 72-58 lead with 11:35 left. Peete and Hatila Passos both finished with 18 points. Peete also had five rebounds for the Aggies. Crevelone led the Mustangs with 18. Clarkson added 17.
